AU  - Xu, Lixin Colin
AU  - Yan, Xiao
T1  - Property rights, political connections, and corporate investment
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfad029
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 28
IS  - 2
SP  - 593
EP  - 619
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We study the impact of an urban land titling program on firm investment in Shenzhen, China. We find that this program increased the investment rate for titling firms, but this positive effect only holds for politically connected firms. Further analysis suggests that the titling effect is more pronounced for those titling firms associated with greater expropriation risk. During program implementation, the connected titling firms increased their investment perhaps because, as observed, they experienced fewer disputes than non-connected titling firms.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfad029
ER  - 



